          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The TiN forming the target material, enriched in 15N,",
                "is deposited on a tantalum backing, the target",
                "thickness is 100 nm, as verified through secondary",
                "neutral mass spectroscopy(the uncertainty on this",
                "measurement is included in the contribution to the",
                "target analysis).The stoichiometry Ti/N, which ranges",
                "from 0.97 to 1.18 according to the target, is measured",
                "for each target with the high Z elastic recoil",
                "detection (ERD) technique. Isotopic abundances between",
                "96% and 99%, according to the target, are deduced",
                "from the observed height of the plateau in the yield of",
                "the 14N(p,g)15O resonance at E = 259 keV and from the",
                "ERD data."
              ]
            }
          ],
